snippet.textDisplay: As I transitioned from a teenager into an adult, I found myself becoming more & more distant to my core of friends. And as time wore on, some of us kept in touch while other like me were left out of the loop. At first it hurt seeing photos of them all together on facebook or whatever. But after a while I started to realize that they weren’t as valuable as I had thought. It’s a part of life that we all have to deal with at some point. And just because you’ve known someone for so long does not mean that they are a true friend.
snippet.textOriginal: As I transitioned from a teenager into an adult, I found myself becoming more & more distant to my core of friends. And as time wore on, some of us kept in touch while other like me were left out of the loop. At first it hurt seeing photos of them all together on facebook or whatever. But after a while I started to realize that they weren’t as valuable as I had thought. It’s a part of life that we all have to deal with at some point. And just because you’ve known someone for so long does not mean that they are a true friend.

He (through Jesus Christ) wants you to come to Him with all of your weaknesses: physical, emotional, and spiritual. Rest in the comfort of His Presence, remembering that nothing is impossible with Jesus. Pry your mind away from your problems so you can focus your attention on our Lord. Understand that He is able to do immeasurably more than all you ask or imagine.             

When anxiety attempts to wedge its way into your thoughts, remind yourself that Jesus Christ is your Comforter and your Shepherd. Receive Him this very moment!!! Though it may feel frightening, the safest place to ever be is in the loving care of Jesus Christ. Acknowledge that you are a sinner in need of a Savior. Confess with your mouth and believe in your heart that Jesus is Lord. Receive grace through faith by believing in Yeshua (Jesus Christ) and what He did on the cross, His death, burial and resurrection. You will then be sealed and justified in salvation. Trust your soul to Jesus and be saved. ❤️❤️❤️                                                                                                                

(Luke 1 : 37; Ephesians 3 : 20-21; Psalms 23 : 1-4;  Ephesians 2 : 6;  John 14 : 27; Matthew 
24 : 30-39; Psalms 34 : 17-19;  Deuteronomy 31 : 6; Isaiah 41 : 10;  Romans 8 : 38-39)
